I am surprised there are so many negative reviews.  I judge a pizza place by their plain pizza - a great pizza should start out delicious with just the dough, sauce and cheese. I can only speak to my own experiences, but I have never been disappointed by the pizza here. The pizza is always freshly made and the cheese is always mouth-watering. I also enjoy the free garlic dipping sauce with every pizza.  The stuffed shells I ordered once were OK but did not taste as fresh as the pizza. I always order carry-out since it is located near my work and they have carry-out specials which save $1-2, so I can’t comment on any delivery issues. The inside is kept clean but it is run-down. I first mistook the place for being shut down due to its sparse furnishings, but it is clearly not a restaurant- it is a kitchen with a counter to order food. Given the quality and value of the pizza, I think it is fair to rate this Pizza Boli’s location as 4 stars.

I disagree with all the negative reviews on here. I was skeptical at first but this is my personnel experience: the store is very very clean, from the building to when I was at the front desk, I could see how clean the kitchen was; the chefs, were all wearing aprons and took all hygienic measures to make sure the food was healthy. I ordered wings, subs and a pizza. Couldn’t be more satisfied with what I paid for. The quality was top notch and the sub was well made with great meat quantity. The wings were great and the cheese pizza was phenomenal. They also gave me as much ranch and ketchup I asked for! Overall, great experience and I would HIGHLY RECOMMEND it! It’s unjust to judge the book by its cover so if you are in the area, it’s a must try!
